---
import LegalLayout from "../layouts/LegalLayout.astro";
const contactEmail = "hello@readystackdigital.com";
---

<LegalLayout
  title="Acceptable Use Policy | ReadyStack Digital"
  description="Rules for using the ReadyStack Digital website, AI assistant and WhatsApp channel fairly and lawfully."
  path="/acceptable-use"
  heading="Acceptable Use Policy"
  updated="30 May 2026"
>
  <p class="legal-lead">
    This policy explains how you may use the ReadyStack Digital website, our AI assistant
    ("Stack"), and our WhatsApp channel. It exists to keep these services safe, reliable
    and useful for everyone. By using them, you agree to this policy. It works alongside
    our <a href="/terms">Terms of Service</a> and <a href="/privacy">Privacy &amp; Cookie Policy</a>.
  </p>

  <h2>What you may do</h2>
  <p>
    Use the website and assistant to learn about our services, ask genuine questions, get
    indicative pricing, capture an enquiry, and book a call.
  </p>

  <h2>What you must not do</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>Use the services for anything unlawful, fraudulent, harmful or misleading.</li>
    <li>Send abusive, harassing, threatening, hateful, obscene or defamatory content.</li>
    <li>Spam, flood, or send repetitive or automated messages, or otherwise disrupt the service.</li>
    <li>Attempt to gain unauthorised access, probe, scan or test the security of our systems, or interfere with their normal operation.</li>
    <li>Reverse engineer, scrape, or use bots to harvest content or overload the service.</li>
    <li>Impersonate any person or organisation, or misrepresent your affiliation.</li>
    <li>Upload or transmit malware, or anything designed to harm or disrupt.</li>
    <li>Submit other people's personal or sensitive information without authority.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Using the AI assistant responsibly</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>Don't attempt to manipulate the assistant with prompt-injection or jailbreak techniques, or try to extract its underlying instructions.</li>
    <li>Don't rely on the assistant for professional, legal, financial, medical or security advice. It provides general information only and may be inaccurate.</li>
    <li>Don't submit payment card details, passwords, government identifiers or other sensitive information through the chat.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Fair use and rate limits</h2>
  <p>
    We apply rate limits and automated abuse protection (including, where needed, an
    invisible Cloudflare Turnstile check) to keep the service available for everyone. If
    you hit a limit, please slow down and try again shortly.
  </p>

  <h2>Consequences of misuse</h2>
  <p>
    If you breach this policy, we may rate-limit, block or restrict your access, remove
    content, and where appropriate report unlawful activity to the relevant authorities.
    We log activity for security and abuse-investigation purposes as described in our
    <a href="/privacy">Privacy &amp; Cookie Policy</a>.
  </p>

  <h2>Reporting misuse</h2>
  <p>
    If you notice abuse, a security issue or anything that looks wrong, please let us know
    at <a href={"mailto:" + contactEmail}>{contactEmail}</a>.
  </p>

  <h2>Changes to this policy</h2>
  <p>
    We may update this policy from time to time. The current version will always be
    available on this page, with the "last updated" date shown above.
  </p>

  <h2>Contact</h2>
  <p>
    Questions about acceptable use? Email
    <a href={"mailto:" + contactEmail}>{contactEmail}</a>.
  </p>
</LegalLayout>
